@NODE "requirements" "WBTicTacToe - Requirements"

@{b}Requirements@{ub}

WBTicTacToe has the following requirements:
  - 68020 or better
  - AmigaOS 3.x
  - The largerboards will require a higher resolution - the largest board goes up to about 500x700 pixels.

WBTicTacToe has been tested on the following machines and found to work fine:
  - AmigaOne XE-G4, OS4.1 Final Edition
  - Amiga 1200 060/66, 192MB, Voodoo 3-3000, OS3.9
  - Amiga 1200 030/50, 32MB, AGA, OS3.1 & OS3.9
  - iBook G4, MorphOS 3.7

If a graphics card isn't detected, the graphics are automatically reduced to a basic 8-colour setting. It tries to allocate red and green pens for the two different players' markers, so it should work fine on almost any setup. If you have too few colours on your screen however you might not be able to tell the players apart...

